This document describes the installation procedure on MacOSX Snow Leopard
10.6.

The installation procedure consists of the steps described below:

Step 1. Prerequisites
Step 2. Install Dependencies
Step 3. Install SIP SIMPLE client SDK


Step 1. Prerequisites
---------------------

 * MacOSX 10.6 (Snow Leopard)
 * Intel 32bit or 64bit architectures
 * Apple Developer tools (XCode)
 * darcs version control tool from http://www.darcs.net

The procedure below relies on the standard available Python interpreter that
comes with MacOSX Snow Leopard (version 2.6). Make sure that during the
building process you are not involving external tools or libraries like the
ones provided by Fink or Darwin Ports distributions.

To change the default python interpreter, to version 2.5 for example:

sudo defaults write com.apple.versioner.python Version 2.5


Architecture
------------

The SIPSIMPLE build process will use the Python interpreter's architecture to
build the executable files. This can be overridden by setting the following
environment variable:

export SIPSIMPLE_OSX_ARCH="i386"


SDK Version
-----------

By default the system version SDK will be used to build SIPSIMPLE SDK. That is,
if you are running Mac OSX 10.6 the 10.6 SDK will be used. This can be overridden
by setting the following environment variable:

export SIPSIMPLE_OSX_SDK="10.5"


Step 2. Install Dependencies
----------------------------

See Dependencies.txt for detailed description of the required libraries and
their minimum version number.

In order to build all libraries with i386 architecture compatible with OSX 10.5
export the following environment variables before starting the build process:

export CC="gcc -isysroot /Developer/SDKs/MacOSX10.5.sdk"
export ARCHFLAGS="-arch i386"
export LDSHARED="gcc -Wl,-F. -bundle -undefined dynamic_lookup -isysroot /Developer/SDKs/MacOSX10.5.sdk"

It is recommended that you do not have fink or darwin ports installed on the
build machine, otherwise the software may be linked against libraries that 
are not present on other systems.  

Build and install C dependencies, the software will be installed under
/usr/local folder:

# Install GNUTLS dependencies
curl -O ftp://ftp.gnupg.org/gcrypt/libgpg-error/libgpg-error-1.7.tar.bz2
tar -xjvf libgpg-error-1.7.tar.bz2
cd libgpg-error-1.7
CFLAGS="-arch i386" ./configure --prefix=/usr/local --disable-static --disable-dependency-tracking
make
sudo make install
cd ..

curl -O http://ftp.gnu.org/pub/gnu/libtasn1/libtasn1-2.2.tar.gz
tar zxvf libtasn1-2.2.tar.gz 
cd libtasn1-2.2
CFLAGS="-arch i386" ./configure --disable-dependency-tracking
make
sudo make install
cd ..

curl -O ftp://ftp.gnupg.org/gcrypt/libgcrypt/libgcrypt-1.4.5.tar.bz2
tar -xjvf libgcrypt-1.4.5.tar.bz2
cd libgcrypt-1.4.5
CFLAGS="-arch i386" ./configure --prefix=/usr/local --with-gpg-error-prefix=/usr/local --disable-static --disable-dependency-tracking --disable-asm
make
sudo make install
cd ..

# Install GNUTLS
curl -O http://ftp.gnu.org/pub/gnu/gnutls/gnutls-2.8.6.tar.bz2
tar -xjvf gnutls-2.8.6.tar.bz2
cd gnutls-2.8.6
CFLAGS="-arch i386" ./configure --prefix=/usr/local --with-libgcrypt-prefix=/usr/local --disable-static --disable-dependency-tracking
make
sudo make install
cd ..


Install Python dependencies by using the easy_install tool. The software
will be installed in /Library/Python/2.6/site-packages for Python 2.6 or in
/Library/Python/2.5/site-packages for Python 2.5.

sudo easy_install -U python-gnutls dnspython twisted \
python-application PIL cython python-dateutil

# Install lxml python module
STATIC_DEPS=true sudo easy_install lxml


Step 3. Install SIP SIMPLE client SDK
-------------------------------------

The SDK consists of four parts:

 1. python-eventlet, python-greenlet, python-backports
 2. XCAP library
 3. MSRP library
 4. SIP SIMPLE library

# Eventlet
if [ -d python-eventlet ]; then
        cd python-eventlet
        darcs pull -a 
        sudo python setup.py install
else
        darcs get http://devel.ag-projects.com/repositories/python-eventlet
        cd python-eventlet
        sudo python setup.py install
fi
cd ..

# Greenlet
if [ -d python-greenlet ]; then
        cd python-greenlet
        darcs pull -a
        sudo python setup.py install
else
        darcs get http://devel.ag-projects.com/repositories/python-greenlet
        cd python-greenlet
